@@TJvDBGrid
<TITLEIMG TJvDBGrid>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.DBAware.GridsTreesLists.Grids
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  Descendant of the standard TDBGrid with additional methods, properties and events.
Description
  Use TJvDBGrid as a replacement for TDBGrid when you need additional control over how the grid component
  works. TJvDBGrid introduces new methods, properties and events to control the appearance and functionality
  of the grid.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.AlternateRowColor
Summary
  Indicates the color to use on odd rows in the grid.
Description
  Use AlternateRowColor to specify a different color for every other row in the grid. Setting AlternateRowColor
  to the same color as the background or to clNone disables the feature.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.AutoAppend
Summary
  Indicates whether moving beyond the last row in the grid, automatically inserts a new row.
Description
  Use AutoAppend to specify whether new records are automatically appended when the user tries to move beyond
  the last row in the grid.
Note
  Due to the design of the base TCustomDBGrid, AutoAppend does not work correctly when dgTabs is in Options and the user
  tabs beyond the last row.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.AutoSizeColumnIndex
Summary
  Indicates the column that will be autosized when the grid or its columns are resized.
Description
  Use AutoSizeColumnIndex to specify the column or columns that are auto sized. AutoSizeColumnIndex can be
  set to any of the following values:

  <TABLE>
  Value   Meaning
  -----   -------
  -2      Indicates that the right-most visible column should be auto sized. If the number of visible columns changes
           so might the column that is sized.
  -1      Auto size all visible columns proportionally.
  0..n    Auto size the column with the specified index. If n >= Columns.Count, autosizing is disabled.
  </TABLE>

  Auto sizing is only active when AutoSizeColumns is true and all visible columns in the grid
  can be shown without a horizontal scrollbar. The values of MinColumnWidth and MaxColumnWidth are
  also taken into consideration when auto sizing.
See Also
  AutoSizeColumns, MinColumnWidth, MaxColumnWidth
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.AutoSizeColumns
Summary
  Indicates whether columns are autosized or not.
Description
  Use AutoSizeColumns to specify whether auto sizing is active or not. The actual column or columns
  that are auto sized are controlled with the AutoSizeColumnIndex property.
See Also
  AutoSizeColumnIndex
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.AutoSort
Summary
  Indicates whether the grid tries to change the sort index of the dataset or not.
Description
  Use AutoSort when you want the grid to sort automatically when a column is clicked (TitleButtons must be set to true).
  If AutoSort is true, the grid can sort the columns automatically if all of the following criteria are true:
    * The dataset has a published property named "\IndexDefs" of type TIndexDefs
    * The dataset has a published property named "\IndexName" of type string
    * There is an index in IndexName that contains the name of the filed of the clicked column
See Also
  SortedField, SortMarker, TitleButtons, OnTitleClick, OnTitleBtnClick
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.BeepOnError
Summary
  Indicates whether the speaker beeps when there is an error.
Description
  Use BeepOnError to specify whether errors in input triggers a speaker beep. The standard DBGrid always
  beeps on errors. Set BeepOnError to false to suppress this behavior.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.ClearSelection
Summary
  Clears the selection in the grid when the user moves to a new cell in MultiSelect mode.
Description
  Set ClearSelection to true to remove any additional selected rows when the user moves to a new
  cell in the grid and MultiSelect is true.
  If ClearSelection is false, multi selected rows remains selected when the user navigates the grid.
See Also
  MultiSelect
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.FixedCols
Summary
  Indicates the number of fixed columns in the grid.
Description
  Set FixedCols to make additional columns in the grid appear as fixed columns. By default, the only
  fixed column in a DB grid is the indicator column.
See Also
  Options, Columns
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.GotoSelection
Summary
  Moves focus to the specified selected row.
Description
  Use GotoSelection to move the focus in a multi selected grid to a new row. When MultiSelect is false or
  no rows are selected, this procedure does nothing.
Parameters
  Index - Index of the selected row. For example: if there are two selected rows, then index 0 moves to the first
  selected row and index 1 to the second.
See Also
  ClearSelection, MultiSelect
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.IniStorage
Summary
  Indicates the application storage component to use to save the grids current settings.
Description
  Assign an existing TJvAppStorage component to this property to have the properties of the grid automatically
  saved and loaded when the application starts and closes down.

  Properties stored include the columns layout as well as the DisplayLabel, DisplayWidth and Visible property
  of all the used fields.
See Also
  Load, LoadFromAppStore, Save, SaveToAppStore
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.Load
Summary
  Load settings from storage.
Description
  Call Load to manually read previously saved settings using IniStorage. If IniStorage is nil, this
  method does nothing.
See Also
  LoadFromAppStore, Save, SaveToAppStore
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.LoadFromAppStore
Summary
  \Load settings from a specific application storage component.
Description
  Use LoadFromAppStore to load settings from a specific TJvAppStorage component instead of using IniStorage.
Parameters
  AppStorage - The TJvAppStorage component to use.
  Path       - The path to the storage location.
See Also
  IniStorage, Load, Save, SaveToAppStore
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.MaxColumnWidth
Summary
  Sets the maximum width of a column.
Description
  Set MaxColumnWidth to a value > 0 to have the grid automatically size columns whose width exceeds MaxColumnWidth.
See Also
  MinColumnWidth
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.MinColumnWidth
Summary
  Sets the minimum width of a column.
Description
  Set MinColumnWidth to a value > 0 to have the grid automatically size columns whose width is less than MinColumnWidth.
See Also
  MaxColumnWidth
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.OnCheckButton
Summary
  Occurs when a title button is clicked.
Description
  Write a handler for this event to conditionally enable and disable title button clicks. Set Enabled to
  true (the default) to enable clicking the title button, set Enabled to false to disable clicking.
Parameters
  Sender  - The grid that triggered the event.
  ACol    - The index of the column.
  Field   - The field of the cell.
  Enabled - Indicates if the button should be enabled or not.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.OnDrawColumnTitle
Summary
  Occurs when a column header is to be drawn.
Description
  Write a handler for the OnDrawColumnTitle to custom draw the title buttons in the grid.
Parameters
  Sender                - The grid that triggered the event.
  ACanvas               - The canvas to draw on.
  ARect                 - The rect area to draw in.
  Field                 - The field of the cell.
##  AFont                 - The cell's font.
##  Background            - The cell's background color.
  ASortMarker           - The sort marker to display.
  IsDown                - Indicates whether the button is down or not.
  Offset                - The default offset of the text
  DefaultDrawText       - Specifies whether the default method should draw the text.
  DefaultDrawSortMarker - Specifies whether the default method should draw the sort marker.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.OnEditChange
Summary
  Occurs when the user makes changes to a cell.
Description
  Write a handler for the OnEditChange event to be notified when the user edits a cell in the grid.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.OnGetBtnParams
Summary
  Occurs when the grid needs additional information for the current header button.
Description
  Write a handler for this event to modify the appearance of the title buttons.
Parameters
  Sender     - The grid that triggered the event.
  Field      - The field of the cell.
  AFont      - The cell's font.
  Background - The cell's background color.
  ASortMarker - The sort marker to display.
  IsDown     - Indicates whether the button is down or not.
See Also
  OnGetCellParams, OnGetCellProps
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.OnGetCellParams
Summary
  Occurs when the grid needs additional information about the current cell.
Description
  Write a handler for this event to provide additional information about the current cell. This event differs
  from OnGetCellProps only in the Highlight parameter.
Parameters
  Sender     - The grid that triggered the event.
  Field      - The field of the cell.
  AFont      - The cell's font.
  Background - The cell's background color.
  Highlight  - Specifies whether the cell should be highlighted or not.
See Also
  OnGetCellProps
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.OnGetCellProps
Summary
  Occurs when the grid needs additional information about the current cell.
Description
  Write a handler for this event to provide additional information about the current cell. This event differs
  from OnGetCellParams only in the Highlight parameter.
Parameters
  Sender     - The grid that triggered the event.
  Field      - The field of the cell.
  AFont      - The cell's font.
  Background - The cell's background color.
See Also
  OnGetCellParams
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.OnShowCellHint
Summary
  Occurs when a cell in the grid wants to display its hint.
Description
  Write a handler for this event to provide custom hints for the cells in the grid. This event is
  only triggered if hints are enabled and ShowCellHint is true.
Parameters
  Sender   - The grid that triggered the event.
  Field    - The field the column displays.
  AHint    - Set this to the hint text to use.
  ATimeOut - The number of milliseconds that should pass before the hint window is hidden.
See Also
  OnShowTitleHint, ShowCellHint
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.OnShowEditor
Summary
  Occurs when the inplace editor is about to be shown.
Description
  Write a handler for this event to conditionally enable and disable cell editing.
Parameters
  Sender    - The grid that triggered the event.
  Field     - The field that is to be edited.
  AllowEdit - Set this to false to prevent editing of the field.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.OnShowTitleHint
Summary
  Occurs when a column header wants to display its hint.
Description
  Write a handler for this event to provide custom hints for title buttons. This event is
  only triggered if hints are enabled and ShowTitleHint is true.
Parameters
  Sender   - The grid that triggered the event.
  Field    - The field the column displays.
  AHint    - Set this to the hint text to use.
  ATimeOut - The number of milliseconds that should pass before the hint window is hidden.
See Also
  OnShowCellHint, ShowTitleHint
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.OnTitleArrowMenuEvent
Summary
  Occurs when the arrow in the indicator column is clicked.
Description
  Write a handler for this event to be notified when the title arrow in the indicator column is clicked.
  This event is only triggered when TitleArrow is true, the titles and indicator row are visible
  and the right mouse button is clicked.
See Also
  TitleArrow, Options
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.OnTitleBtnClick
Summary
  Occurs when a column header button is clicked.
Description
  Write a handler for this event to be notified when a title button is clicked.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.OnTitleBtnDblClick
Summary
  Occurs when a column header button is double-clicked.
Description
  Write a handler for this event to be notified when a title button is double-clicked. Note that the
  OnTitleBtnClick event will also be triggered by a double-click.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.PostOnEnter
Summary
  Specifies whether pressing the Enter key posts the changes to the dataset.
Description
  Use PostOnEnter to specify whether pressing the Enter key automatically posts data to the underlying dataset.
  If PostOnEnter is false, the user must move to another cell before the modified data is committed.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.Save
Summary
  Save settings to storage.
Description
  Call Save to manually save the grid settings to IniStorage. If IniStorage is nil, this method does nothing.
See Also
  IniStorage
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.SaveToAppStore
Summary
  \Save settings to a specific application storage component.
Description
  Use SaveToAppStore to save settings to a specific TJvAppStorage component instead of using IniStorage.
Parameters
  AppStorage - The TJvAppStorage component to use.
  Path       - The path to the storage location.
See Also
  IniStorage, Save, Load, LoadFromAppStore
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.SelCount
Summary
  Indicates the number of rows selected.
Description
  Read SelCount to learn the number of selected rows in the grid. SelCount is always <= 1 when
  MultiSelect is false.
See Also
  MultiSelect
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.SelectAll
Summary
  Selects all rows in the grid.
Description
  Call SelectAll to select all rows in the grid. If MultiSelect is false, this method does nothing.
See Also
  UnselectAll, MultiSelect
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.SelectColumn
Summary
  Indicates the item order in the select column dialog.
Description
  Use SelectColumn to specify the order of items in the select column dialog. When SelectColumn is scDatabase,
  the fields in the dialog are displayed in the same order as in the dataset. When SelectColumn is scGrid, the
  fields are displayed in the same order as they appear in the grid's Columns collection.
See Also
  ShowColumnsDialog, SelectColumnsDialogStrings
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.SelectColumnsDialogStrings
Summary
  Indicates the strings to use for the select column dialog.
Description
  SelectColumnsDialogStrings manages the strings used by the select column dialog. When localizing, change the
  string properties of this class to the currently selected language.
See Also
  ShowColumnsDialog
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.ShowCellHint
Summary
  Indicates whether hints are displayed for cells in the grid.
Description
  Use ShowCellHint to indicate whether cells in the grid should display their own custom hints. To actually
  display a hint text, assign a handler to the OnShowCellHint event.
See Also
  OnShowCellHint
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.ShowColumnsDialog
Summary
  Displays the select column dialog.
Description
  Call ShowColumnsDialog to manually bring up the select column dialog. The select column dialog is used
  to modify the visible state of the columns in the grid.
See Also
  TitleArrow, OnTitleArrowMenuEvent
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.ShowGlyphs
Summary
  Indicates whether the grid displays images or not.
Description
  Set ShowGlyphs to true to replace the field content of blob and memo fields with an image. If ShowGlyphs
  is false, the grid displays the default text strings, like "(Memo)" and "(Blob)" instead.

  The grid will display custom images for the following field types:

  ftBytes, ftVarBytes, ftBlob, ftTypedBinary, ftOraBlob<P>
  ftMemo, ftOraClob<P>
  ftGraphic <P>
  ftParadoxOle, ftDBaseOle<P>
  ftCursor, ftReference, ftDataSet<P>
  ftBoolean
Note
  If the OnGetText and OnSetText events are assigned, ShowGlyphs does nothing.
See Also
  TField.OnGetText, TField.OnSetText
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.ShowTitleHint
Summary
  Indicates whether hints are displayed for column headers.
Description
  Use ShowTitleHint to indicate whether title buttons should display their own custom hints. To actually
  display a hint text, assign a handler to the OnShowTitleHint event.
See Also
  OnShowTitleHint
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.SortedField
Summary
  Specifies the field to display a sort marker for.
Description
  Use SortedField to indicate the field that should be used to sort the grid. If the dataset in use
  has the properties 'IndexDefs' and 'IndexName' and IndexDefs contains a definition for the value in
  SortedField, IndexName will be changed automatically to the value of SortedField when a title button
  is clicked.
See Also
  AutoSort, OnTitleBtnClick
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.SortMarker
Summary
  Specifies the sort arrow to display for the currently sorted column.
Description
  Use SortMarker to indicate the sort arrow to display for the current sort column. The current sort column
  is determined by the value of the SortedField property. Note that setting SortedField and SortMaker does not
  guarantee that the column will be sorted. For an explanation of when the grid can sort the columns automatically,
  see the AutoSort topic.
See Also
  AutoSort, SortedField, TitleButtons, OnTitleBtnClick
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.TitleArrow
Summary
  Specifies whether a down pointing arrow is displayed in the indicator column.
Description
  Use TitleArrow to indicate whether the indicator column displays a down pointing arrow or not.
  When TitleArrow is true, clicking the arrow displays the select column dialog.
See Also
  ShowColumnsDialog
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.TitleButtons
Summary
  Indicates whether column headers can be clicked or not.
Description
  Use TitleButtons to specify whether title button clicking is enabled or not.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.TitleOffset
Summary
  Indicates the offset from the left edge to the first "real" column.
Description
  Read TitleOffset to get the index of the first visible column in the grid.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.TitlePopup
Summary
  Specifies the popup menu to use for column headers.
Description
  Set TitlePopup to an existing popup menu to use it as the popup menu for the title buttons in the grid.
See Also
  PopupMenu
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.ToggleRowSelection
Summary
  Toggles the currently selected row on and off.
Description
  Call ToggleRowSelection to toggle SelectedRows.CurrentRowSelected on and off. If MultiSelect is false,
  this method does nothing.
See Also
  ClearSelection, GotoSelection, MultiSelect
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDBGrid.UnselectAll
Summary
  Removes any selection.
Description
  Call UnselectAll to remove any selection in the grid. If MultiSelect is false, this method does nothing.
See Also
  ClearSelection, GotoSelection, MultiSelect, SelectAll, ToggleRowSelection
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
